o make payments to them SEPARATELY, the payments always just get globbed together and applied to one account or the other, therefore marking my other account delinquent. Super fun to deal with. There is also no way to track your payment history through the website to show them you ARE NOT delinquent, and your payments take a MINIMUM of 7 days to post (they say maximum of 7 days but it's usually more like 10 or 15). Seriously? How is it that any other medical facility I have been to can manage to post payments faster than a two week turnaround time? I e-mailed for assistance, was told my information was being forwarded to the correct department because they "could not assist me with my question" (how would the "contact patient billing" option lead me to someone who couldn't assist me with a patient billing question?), and never heard back. Have e-mailed them again, and of course, have not heard back. Good luck calling them either.  Praying if I, God forbid, end up in the ED again any time soon that Chandler is not the closest hospital. Dignity Health, you have completely ruined the back office functions of a previously awesome facility. Congrats.

